This adds two new configuration options for modules:

1. `env` lets a module configure the guest environment (useful e.g. for setting up a `PATH`);
2. `copy` lets a module place additional files in the guest environment (useful e.g. for copying resource files).

This is something of an emergency patch, as https://github.com/matrix-org/synapse/issues/11385 breaks the workflow.

Several features in a single bundle:
- in mx-tester.yaml, `up` may now contain two fields `before` and `after`;
- we may now pick any released version of Synapse, rather than the latest;
- we now run the Synapse docker image as current user, rather than using the `UID`/`GID` environment variables.

This patch:
- replaces std::io::Error with anyhow::Error;
- removes almost all uses of unwrap() and except();
- annotates errors for better error contexts.
